      "timestamp": "2026-05-08T01:40:20.721+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "hm? not sure I understand the question.\n\nMy reading of the DRC so far is that the only way to make SiN openings is with the pad rules, and those have to be 40um at the moment which is far too large for \"structured asic\" / \"gate array\" sort of customization after fab. But I've only started looking into it so may be incorrect with that assumption!",
