      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "> Not recommended to use 6k top metal for cu wire bonding.\n\nI just read this; does it mean we could use a wire bonder (or possibly less hyper-specialized thermosonic micro welding robot/head) to form/attach copper pillars to the otherwise \"normal\" pads which would then be suited for reasonably normal soldering metallurgy? Because the normal aluminum is not really solderable and (electro/-less) chemical plating seems difficult after dicing.",
